                    }
                </style>
                
<a href="/photo/2015/04/the-vietnam-war-part-iii-hands-of-a-nation/389309/">
    <figure>
        <div class="lead-image"></div>
        <figcaption class="credit">Eddie Adams/AP</figcaption>
    </figure>
</a>

<ul class="metadata">
    <li class="kicker">In Focus</li>
    <li class="date">Apr 1, 2015</li>
    <li class="num-photos">26 Photos</li>
</ul>

<h1 class="hed">
    <a href="/photo/2015/04/the-vietnam-war-part-iii-hands-of-a-nation/389309/">
        The Vietnam War, Part III: Hands of a Nation
    </a>
</h1>
<p class="dek"><span>The photojournalist Eddie Adams, who covered the Vietnam War for the Associated Press, not only captured the action and chaos but </span><span>took the time to get up close to the Vietnamese people whenever he could. </span></p>

            </li>
            
            <li id="recent4" class="grid-article recent-article">
                <style type="text/css">
                    #recent4 .lead-image {
                        
                        background-image: url(http://cdn.theatlantic.com/assets/media/img/photo/2015/03/the-vietnam-war-part-ii-losses-and/v01_AP690411056-1/river_thumb.jpg);
                    }
                </style>
                
<a href="/photo/2015/03/the-vietnam-war-part-ii-losses-and-withdrawal/389192/">
    <figure>
        <div class="lead-image"></div>
        <figcaption class="credit">Horst Faas/AP</figcaption>
    </figure>
</a>

<ul class="metadata">
    <li class="kicker">In Focus</li>
    <li class="date">Mar 31, 2015</li>
    <li class="num-photos">50 Photos</li>
</ul>

<h1 class="hed">
    <a href="/photo/2015/03/the-vietnam-war-part-ii-losses-and-withdrawal/389192/">
        The Vietnam War, Part II: Losses and Withdrawal
    </a>
</h1>
<p class="dek"><span>Tactically, the 1968 Tet Offensive was a huge loss for the North, but it marked a significant turning point in public opinion and political support, leading to a draw</span><span>down of U.S. </span><span>troop involvement, </span><span>and eventual withdrawal in 1973.</span></p>

            </li>
            
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

